title: What Is the Power of Unity Phelan’s Dancing? ‘I’m Clay.’
description: Phelan, a principal at New York City Ballet, has gone from rising to risen with a stellar fall season that has shown her range in a string of debuts.
dc:creator: Gia Kourlas
media:credit: Josefina Santos for The New York Times
media:description: Unity Phelan, a principal dancer at New York City Ballet, has had a season of debuts in important roles. “What I feel strongly about is that I want to be unaffected and as pure as it possibly can be.”
